mcc Compile MATLAB functions for deployment outside MATLAB. 
 mcc [-options] fun [fun2...]

Options applicable across all deployment targets: 
 -? Display help for the mcc command 
 -a Add additional files or directories to be included in the build 
 -d Build output directory 
 -g Include debugging symbol information 
 -I Add a directory to be searched for MATLAB files 
 -v Verbose display of build

MATLAB Compiler 
 Standalone Application (MATLAB|Hadoop|Spark)
 mcc -m <matlabFile.m> 
 
 Excel Add-In 
 mcc -W 'excel:<addinName>,<className>' -b <matlabFile.m> 
 
 Hadoop Deployable Archive 
 mcc -H -W 'hadoop:<archiveName>,CONFIG:<configFile.txt>' <mapperFile.m> <reducerFile.m> <datastoreInfo.mat> 
 
 Spark Application 
 mcc -C -W 'spark:<appName>,<sparkMajorVersion>' <matlabFile.m>

MATLAB Compiler SDK 
 C Shared Library 
 mcc -W lib:<libraryName> <matlabFile.m> 
 
 C++ Shared Library 
 mcc -W cpplib:<libraryName> <matlabFile.m> 
 
 .NET Assembly 
 mcc -W 'dotnet:<assemblyName>,<className>' <matlabFile.m> 
 
 Java Package 
 mcc -W 'java:<packageName>,<className>' <matlabFile.m> 
 
 Python Package 
 mcc -W python:<pythonPackageName> <matlabFile.m> 
 
 COM Component 
 mcc -W com:<componentName> <matlabFile.m>

MATLAB Production Server 
 Deployable Archive 
 mcc -W CTF:<archiveName> -U <matlabFile.m> 
 
 Deployable Archive for Excel Add-In 
 mcc -W mpsxl:<addinName> <matlabFile.m>

The -F switch is no longer supported.
The -L switch is no longer supported; the target (-T) and wrapper (-W) \nswitches determine the language of the generated code. \n
The -O switch is no longer supported; the MATLAB JIT accelerator makes \nCompiler optimizations unnecessary. \n
The -V switch is no longer supported; the MATLAB Compiler does not allow the use of previous compiler versions.
The -h switch is no longer supported; the MATLAB Compiler detects MATLAB file \ndependencies automatically. But see also the documentation for the -a switch.
The -i switch is no longer supported; the "include exported interfaces" behavior \nis applied to every compilation. \n

The -t switch is no longer supported; the Compiler no longer generates C/C++ 
source code for MATLAB functions (it generates wrapper functions instead, see 
the documentation for -W).
The -z switch is no longer supported. \n
The -win32 switch is no longer supported. \n
The -win64 switch is no longer supported; 64-bit architecture is assumed. \n
